children.text: The sub-floor ventilation is being obstructed, resulting in a damp environment, which according to the BCA, encourages timber rot, fungus growth and the potential for termite activity.
Part 3.4.1.2 of the National Construction Code’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) states that

‘Subfloor spaces must be provided with openings in external walls and internal subfloor walls in accordance with Table 3.4.1.1’, and that ‘openings must be aligned to allow an unobstructed flow of air’.
The builder will need to remove the obstructions to increase the ventilation in accordance with part 3.4.1.2 of the BCA.
